Apr 14 2009 	Good DT Chicago Base For Our Family; Great Staff	Our family decided to try this Residence Inn as our base for doing the standard Chicago museum-viewing tourist stay, and we're glad we did. Among similar properties, this gave us the best package deal for what we wanted-- AAA rates plus parking provided a king suite, breakfasts, a pool, and an exercise room.Staff from valet parking in through valet parking out, and everywhere in between, were exceptionally courteous and did their jobs well. The entire hotel was clean and maintained well. The amenities of the Residence Inn chain were all there-- the kitchenettes, the multiple options for breakfast, the weeknight evening foods....During our stay, we didn't find the place overly crowded, and thus our breakfast and pool experiences weren't lessened by mobs. One of the two common-area computers was available the two nights I wanted to check transit routes.Some notes: swimming pool is small (but open by 6:30 a.m.), You're a short walk from a drug store / grocery store, Starbucks (though house coffee is tolerable), and multiple dining options and major transit hubs are a short walk away (and you can catch a bus route right outside the hotel). Be forewarned a fire station is 1.5 blocks away (but even closer to other hotels), so you're likely to get at least a siren during the night.Remember you're in a big US city and prices/facilities reflect it; just plan for it, and bring tip money for the staff willing to serve you. We'd likely return to this place for similar-style Chicago vacations.	
