Jun 21 2008 	A comfortable property in a vibrant location	We visited this brand new property the week after Memorial Day and were thoroughly impressed. Our suite was spacious and elegantly decorated with art deco flourishes. The service, starting from the car valet to the front desk to the cleaning staff, was flawless, friendly, and without attitude. I wish I could say the same about my previous visits to the Pen and some of the other overpriced &quot;lux&quot; properties off &quot;Boul. Mich.&quot;The suite's kitchen (equipped with range top, microwave, full size fridge, &amp; dishwasher) gave us latitude in getting quality, economical meals at Whole Foods Market 4 blocks away. Doing so let us occasionally splurge at the many quality restaurants nearby--do try a deep-dish pizza at Lou Malnati's 3 blocks away!The property's River North location makes it easy to walk everywhere. Michigan Avenue and its wealth of shopping is a 5 minute walk, as are the vibrant restaurants and establishments of Rush St; the Art Institute and Millennium Park are 20 minutes away by foot. For those less inclined to walk, there is a bounty of cabs eager to spirit you away.Surrounding you wherever you go will be magnificent urban architecture that is constantly evolving and the best antidote for suburban boredom. Be sure to bring a camera!	
